                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d7">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #8v #16r #24v #35r #43r #49v #59r #70v #79r #85r #98v #111r #114r #120v #126v #140r #168v" facs="008 016 023 032 042 050 057 066 078 086 092 106 118 121 128 134 147 176">folss. 1r, 8v, 16r, 24v, 35r, 43r, 49v, 59r, 70v, 79r, 85r, 98v, 111r, 114r, 120v, 126v, 140r, 168v, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#1r #8r #42v #49r #84v #98r #126r #139v #161v" facs="008 015 050 056 092 105 133 147 169">1r, 8r, 42v, 49r, 84v, 98r, 126r, 139v, 161v, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#53r" facs="060">53r, </locus> (line of red dots);
                    <locus target="#110v #120r" facs="118 127">110v, 120r</locus> (multiple full stops between lines of red and black dots).
                    A few of the harags are similar to those produced in the government scriptorium
                    </decoNote>
